      {
        "id": 2201248,
        "name": "Alan Rath",
        "username": "Alan_Rath",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/alan_rath/{size}/644_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-06-14T23:00:10.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Enjoyable read! If you ever do a follow, would be interesting to get more of the story of their oak regime and barrel making. I chatted briefly with Paul and Eric at a recent event, where they talked about the long outdoor aging process, and how they think that tames the wood notes; and how they continue to do comparisons between French and American oak, and continue to prefer American.</p>",
        "post_number": 8,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 10,
        "updated_at": "2022-06-02T23:30:25.274Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
