      {
        "id": 2201804,
        "name": "William Kelley",
        "username": "William_Kelley",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/william_kelley/{size}/2314_2.png",
        "created_at": "2017-06-15T20:32:56.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"Alan Rath\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n Alan Rath:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Enjoyable read! If you ever do a follow, would be interesting to get more of the story of their oak regime and barrel making. I chatted briefly with Paul and Eric at a recent event, where they talked about the long outdoor aging process, and how they think that tames the wood notes; and how they continue to do comparisons between French and American oak, and continue to prefer American.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>That\u2019s definitely on the cards. I could have gone into more depth but the blog has to make do with snatched moments here and there and the piece had already gotten quite long. I may well be back at Ridge in August so can ask some questions then.</p>\n<p>In the meantime, have you seen Kelli White\u2019s interesting in-depth piece on American oak, which includes some Ridge insights? <a href=\"https://www.guildsomm.com/public_content/features/features/b/kelli-white/posts/american-oak\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">GuildSomm International</a></p>",
